    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nBracketed paste prevents pasting normal mode commands into a vim window and having them execute.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would like to be able to toggle off bracketed paste such that normal mode commands can be pasted into a nvim normal mode as with vim. Bracketed paste removes an emergent behavior in vim (the ability to paste normal mode commands into the vim session and have those command executed.) This is a fairly powerful feature and I find bracketed paste to be far less useful. Entering Insert mode is trivial in order to achieve the same effect. However, there are so many amazing features in nevoid that I don't want to be forced to go back to vim to ",
